'''「今日俄羅斯」國際新聞通訊社'''（{{lang-rus|''Россия Сегодня''|r=Rossíya Segódnya|p=rɐˈsʲijə sʲɪˈvodʲnʲə}}，{{lang-en|''Rossiya Segodnya''}}<ref name=kremlin1>[[克里姆林宮|克里姆林宮]]官網：
*{{Cite press release |url=http://kremlin.ru/events/president/news/53082 |script-title=ru: Интервью Владимира Путина МИА «Россия сегодня» и информагентству IANS |publisher= |date=2016-10-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803184814/http://kremlin.ru/events/president/news/53082 |archivedate=2020-08-03 |accessdate= |language= |deadurl=no }}
*{{Cite press release |url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/53082 |script-title=en: Interview to Rossiya Segodnya International News Agency and IANS News Agency |publisher= |date=2016-10-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405011303/http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/53082 |archivedate=2020-04-05 |accessdate= |language= |deadurl=no }}</ref>），是[[俄羅斯總統|俄羅斯總統]][[普丁|普丁]]於2013年12月9日簽署命令立案，將官方媒體整合以[[俄新社|俄新社]]為基礎而設立的新聞通訊社<ref>{{cite web |url=http://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2013/12/9/putin-dissolves-rianovostinewsagency.html |title=Putin dissolves RIA Novosti news agency |last1=Pizzi |first1=Michael |date=December 9, 2013 |publisher=[[Al_Jazeera_America|Al Jazeera America]] |accessdate=2017-01-18 |archive-date=2017-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018151550/http://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2013/12/9/putin-dissolves-rianovostinewsagency.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=ru>{{cite book  |title=《俄羅斯公共外交與地緣政治：烏克蘭危機之下普京時代的再造》 |author=胡逢瑛、吳非 | publisher=獨立作家 |page= 51 |url= |chapter=第一章 俄羅斯的「軟實力」與「公共外交」在國際環境中的啟示 |chapterurl={{google books|5DlLDAAAQBAJ|page=51|plainurl=yes}} |date=2016-07-01 |isbn = 978-988-8307-26-5 |language=}}</ref>。不過，俄新社英文版在其立案時報導指出國家似乎表明強化控制已嚴格監管的媒體業。<ref name=rian>[[卫星通讯社|俄罗斯卫星网]]：
*{{cite news |title=RIA Novosti to be liquidated in state-owned media overhaul |url=https://sputniknews.com/russia/20131209185390572-Russia-Announces-State-Owned-Media-Overhaul/ |date=2013-12-09 |accessdate=2017-02-07 |agency=[[卫星通讯社|Sputnik]] ([[RIA_Novosti|RIA Novosti]]) |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131185553/https://sputniknews.com/russia/20131209185390572-Russia-Announces-State-Owned-Media-Overhaul/ |archivedate=2017-01-31 |language= |deadurl=no }}
